{
  "text": "Statistical analysis was performed using a commercial software package (SPSS 17.0, Chicago, IL). This sample size for the study was based on tramadol consumption in the PACU after UPPP surgery, assuming a requirement of rescue tramadol 0.72 (SD0.23) mg/kg with dexmedetomidine-ketaminebased anesthesia [CITATION_1] . To detect a 30% reduction in tramadol requirements in the PACU after surgery, 60 subjects per treatment group would be needed for a study with an alpha level of 0.05 and a beta level of 0.2 (80% power). Sample size was increased by 15% to account for the miss rate.",
